Question: In LaTeX, which combination of packages and commands would allow you to correctly typeset the character 'ǚ' (u with umlaut and caron) when using pdflatex?

A) \usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}
   \usepackage{ucs}
   \unichar{474}

B) \usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}
